{"id":21,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":21,"title":"Chapter 18: Alma the Younger Repents","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 18"],["h1","Alma the Younger Repents"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p3"},"King Mosiah made Alma the leader of the Church in Zarahemla. Alma then chose other men to help him teach the Nephites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/25.19"},"Mosiah 25:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/26.8"},"Mosiah 26:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p5"},"Alma and King Mosiah worried because unbelievers were making Church members suffer because of their beliefs."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.1"},"Mosiah 27:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p7"},"Alma had a son named Alma. Alma the Younger did not believe the teachings of his father and became a wicked man."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.8"},"Mosiah 27:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p9"},"Alma the Younger and the four sons of King Mosiah fought against the Church. They persuaded many people to leave the Church and become wicked."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.8"},"Mosiah 27:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p11"},"Alma prayed that his son would learn the truth and repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.14"},"Mosiah 27:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p13"},"Alma the Younger and the sons of King Mosiah continued trying to destroy the Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.10"},"Mosiah 27:10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p15"},"One day an angel appeared to them. The angel spoke in a loud voice that shook the ground."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.11"},"Mosiah 27:11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p17"},"The five young men were so frightened that they fell down. At first they could not understand what the angel was saying."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.12"},"Mosiah 27:12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p19"},"The angel had come in answer to the prayers of Church members. The angel asked Alma the Younger why he was fighting against the Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.13-14"},"Mosiah 27:13–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p21"},"The ground shook as the angel told Alma the Younger to stop trying to destroy the Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.15-16"},"Mosiah 27:15–16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p23"},"Alma the Younger and the sons of Mosiah fell down again. They had seen an angel, and they knew the power of God had shaken the ground."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.18"},"Mosiah 27:18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p25"},"Alma the Younger was so astonished that he could not speak. He became so weak that he could not even move his hands."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.19"},"Mosiah 27:19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p27"},"The sons of Mosiah carried Alma the Younger to his father and told him all that had happened to them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.19-20"},"Mosiah 27:19–20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p29"},"Alma was happy. He knew that God had answered his prayers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.20"},"Mosiah 27:20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p31"},"Alma called many people together to see what the Lord had done for his son and for the sons of Mosiah."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.21"},"Mosiah 27:21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p33"},"Alma, along with other Church leaders, fasted and prayed and asked God to help Alma the Younger become strong again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.22"},"Mosiah 27:22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p35"},"After two days and nights, Alma the Younger was able to speak and move."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.23"},"Mosiah 27:23"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_18.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p37"},"He told the people he had repented of his sins and God had forgiven him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p38"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.24"},"Mosiah 27:24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f19"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_19.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p39"},"He taught that everyone must become righteous in order to enter God’s kingdom. He also told of the great pain he had suffered because of his sins."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p40"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.25-26,29"},"Mosiah 27:25–26, 29"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f20"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_20.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p41"},"Alma the Younger was happy because he had repented and God had forgiven him. He knew God loved him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p42"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.28"},"Mosiah 27:28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_21.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p43"},"Alma the Younger and the sons of King Mosiah began to teach the truth throughout the land, telling everyone what they had seen and heard."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.32"},"Mosiah 27:32"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_22.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p45","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p45"},"They tried to undo the wrong they had done. They explained the scriptures to the people and taught them about Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p46","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p46"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.35"},"Mosiah 27:35"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.f23"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_021_23.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p47"},"God blessed Alma the Younger and the sons of Mosiah as they taught the gospel. Many people listened to them and believed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-18-alma-the-younger-repents.p48"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.36"},"Mosiah 27:36"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
